      <div class="bio-content">
        <h1>Bengal Tiger</h1>
        <p class="status endangered big">Endangered</p>
        <p><strong>Estimated remaining:</strong> ~2,500</p>

        <h3>Habitat</h3>
        <p>Diverse habitats across India, Bangladesh, Nepal, and Bhutan including mangrove swamps (Sundarbans), dry thorn forests, moist deciduous forests, and grasslands.</p>

        <h3>Threats</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Habitat loss and fragmentation</li>
          <li>Human-wildlife conflict</li>
          <li>Poaching for skins and body parts</li>
          <li>Prey depletion</li>
          <li>Climate change affecting coastal habitats</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Conservation efforts</h3>
        <p>Project Tiger in India has established over 50 tiger reserves. Community-based conservation programs reduce human-tiger conflict. Anti-poaching squads and camera trap monitoring help protect populations. Transboundary conservation between India, Nepal, and Bhutan.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
